          "description": "Variance remained extremely high (-8%) but began a slight descent as the shock of the 'new' wore off and the aesthetic settled into imperial permanence. The 'Paradise' edition extended the mythos into darker, biblical territory ('Garden of Eden' metaphors), but the specific 'Americana' focus shifted slightly toward 'Tropical Noir'. The catalyst for sustaining this high variance was the involvement in The Great Gatsby soundtrack, which institutionally validated her brand of nostalgia as the definitive sound of the Jazz Age revival. This synergy between her personal aesthetic and a major American literary adaptation solidified the cluster as 'High Culture' rather than just internet pastiche.",
