          "description": "The cluster experienced a massive resurgence (+33%) with the release of Norman Fucking Rockwell!. This was not a return to the Born to Die aesthetic, but a mature, complex deconstruction of it. The catalyst was the partnership with Jack Antonoff and a lyrical shift toward 'The Great American Novel' tradition. The variance peaked because she successfully pivoted the 'Americana' cluster from 'pastiche' to 'legacy'; she was no longer cosplaying the 1950s, she was embodying a contemporary, dying California. The 'Norman Rockwell' title itself served as an ironic, melancholic anchor, framing the entire project as an elegy for the American Dream.",
